commit.message: pt: add option for reading virt and physical memory
pt: move arch higher in readme and add pt_host mention

pt_host: add a frontend to pt_dump for the host machine

This patch adds a new frontend, pt_host, that allows dumping the
bound page table for a running Linux process. Currently, only
the x86_64 archtecture is supported. All of the pt_dump commands
are technically supported, but not all are tested.

Example usage:
- sudo ./pt_host.py -pid 12345 -phys_verbose
- sudo ./pt_host.py -pid 12345 -filter x s

pt: abstract machine info gathering and add gdb implementation

The changes are the following:
- Add a "Machine" abstraction for reading physical memory
  and registers
- Add a QEMU-GDB based implementation of the Machine
- Clean-up code to use the Machine interface. This clean-ups
  the code from using the gdb python3 module.

tests: add support for riscv64

For #11

pt: fix riscv64 printing and walk

This patch fixes usage of gdb-pt-dump for riscv64:
- printing is now fixed
- "pt -walk VA" is implemented

tests: add common files

For #11

tests: improve integration tests

This patch does the following:
- Adds a fixture to handle init and deinit
- Parametrize Linux kernel image to handle Linux and arch pecularities
  like KPTI and aarch64 page granules.
- Update aarch64's default base image addr to be a list of possible
  addresses.
- Add two debug env variables: GDB_PT_DUMP_TESTS_PAUSE_AFTER_BOOT
  and GDB_PT_DUMP_TESTS_PAUSE_AFTER_BOOT

For issue #11

pt: rework aarch64 traversal and kaslr

Part of this fixes #15
pt: remove _s and _u

tests: add test for x86_32

This patch adds a simple x86_32 test that covers
pt and pt -ss. The Kolibri OS was chosen since I
had a local floppy image and the OS is fairly
small.

For issue #11

pt: update x86_64 and x86_32 backend selection logic

This patch removes the x86_32 backend and unifies page table
parsing for x86_64 and x86_32. There is still some code that
branches off between 32-bit and 64-bit mode but this seems to
be cleaner than adding more abstraction for PML4 and PDP parsing.

The EFER long mode flag is chosen to select which architecture
should be used every time the page table is parsed. This
guarantees gdb_pt_dump always sees the current architectural state
of the VM.

tests: add phys_verbose tests

This patch adds a basic smoke test for the '-phys_verbose'
command, as well as a few golden tests.

For issue #8

pt: add command '-phys_verbose' for x86 and aarch64

This patch adds the command '-phys_verbose' that prints out
the start physical addresses alongside each virtual range.

Using this command further restricts virtual range merging
which results in more verbose output.

For issue #8
pt: Print stack trace on exception

tests: add walk tests

This patch adds tests to cover the 'pt -walk VA' command.

For issue #8

pt: implement '-walk VA' feature for x86_64 and aarch64

This patch implements the 'pt -walk VA' command for x86_64
and aarch64. The command prints out the translation stages
for a VA: the used table index, physical address and flags.

Example:

pt -walk 0xffff000000000000

Page table walk for VA = 0xffff000000000000
-------------------------------------------
TTBR1_EL1 = 0x4180f000
  Level0[0] = 0x5dffa000          | Flags 0x003
    Level1[0] = 0x5dff9000        | Flags 0x003
      Level2[0] = 0x5dff8000      | Flags 0x003
        Level3[0] = 0x40000000    | Flags 0x707

For issue #8

Add integration tests for aarch64

This patch adds integration tests for aarch64. This is done by
abstracting the test infra to support more than a single vm arch
and then parametrizing the existing integration tests.

This patch also adds a small aarch64 bios for setting up page
tables. This bios is used for the pre-existing aarch64 golden
image testing. Currently, only 3 golden tests are added:
test_granularity_4k, test_granularity_16k, test_granularity_64k

Patch is for issue #11

Add custom kernels for golden image testing

This patch adds the infrastructure to generate custom
x86_64 kernels that enter long mode and a generate page
table. Each generated kernel binary generates a single
page table that is chosen at compile time.

For example, this patch adds these 3 tests for page table
generation:
- x86_64_test_entry_setup_4k_page_table_simple.bin
- x86_64_test_entry_setup_4k_page_table_complex.bin
- x86_64_test_entry_setup_2mb_page_table_simple.bin
Each binary is a floppy-disk image.

The binaries can be used to have the QEMU VM's page tables
in a deterministic state. The output can be used to generate
audited golden images that can be in the future compared
against when running integration tests.

Patch is for issue #11
Fix bug in physmap range reporting for x86

Add integration tests

This patch adds minimal integration test infrastructure for
x86_64 and adds 20 integration tests to cover the following
commands under x86_64:
- pt
- pt -kaslr
- pt -has
- pt -after
- pt -before
- pt -range
- pt -filter ...
- pt -ss, pt -s4, p4 -s8
